Why Git was slow specifically on your machine
Three compounding factors:

Binary files (no delta compression)

iCloud-synced directory

Finder/iCloud interferes with file locks

Large R objects (.rds)

This is not a Git bug.

Sanity check: is Git still working?
If you ever wonder whether Git is frozen, run in another terminal:

bash
Copy code
top | grep git
You’ll see it chewing CPU.

Final takeaway (important)
Git is for code, not data.

For your project:

Code → Git

Results → Excel / disk

Large datasets → ignored

If you ever need versioned data → Git-LFS (not needed here)

